inside
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="350436EFFF97A17EFBD041C25594FE99" blockId="3.[1126,1429,250,269]" box="[1126,1429,250,269]" pageId="3" pageNumber="389">
<bibCitation id="E0913E83FF97A17EFBD041C25594FE99" box="[1126,1429,250,269]" issue="4" journal="Acarologia" page="387" pageId="3" pageNumber="389" score="5.405330260433823" volume="55" year="2015">Acarologia 55(4): 387–396 (2015)</bibCitation>
</paragraph>
<caption id="61C46667FF97A17EFF2944B7537CFA2A" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5402579" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5402579" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5402579/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="389" startId="3.[159,171,1423,1442]" targetBox="[265,1323,302,1391]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="350436EFFF97A17EFF2944B7537CFA2A" blockId="3.[159,1429,1422,1470]" pageId="3" pageNumber="389">
FIGURE 1: 
<taxonomicName id="F2BB4D6CFF97A17EFEB244B75244FA36" authority="Amrine &amp; Stasny, 1994" authorityName="Amrine &amp; Stasny" authorityYear="1994" box="[260,581,1422,1442]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aceria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cortii">
<emphasis id="07CFEAFDFF97A17EFEB244B7516CFA35" box="[260,365,1423,1442]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="389">Aceria cortii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="512A4B1EFF97A17EFEC444B65244FA36" author="Amrine Jr. J. W. &amp; Stasny T. A." box="[370,581,1422,1442]" pageId="3" pageNumber="389" refId="ref4118" refString="Amrine Jr. J. W., Stasny T. A. 1994 - Catalog of the Eriophyoidea (Acarina: Prostigmata) of the world - West Bloomfield, Michigan: Indira. 798 pp." type="book" year="1994">Amrine &amp; Stasny, 1994</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
– Female. AV, anterior ventral aspect; DA, dorsal anterior aspect; DC, dorsal caudal aspect; E, empodium; IGF, internal genital structures of female; L1, leg I; L2, leg II.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="350436EFFF97A17EFF2944C7510CF983" blockId="3.[159,269,1535,1559]" box="[159,269,1535,1559]" pageId="3" pageNumber="389">her body.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="350436EFFF97A17EFF73470D51ACF923" blockId="3.[159,762,1589,1719]" pageId="3" pageNumber="389">
Relation to host — This species is a gall inducer on leaves and young stems of 
<emphasis id="07CFEAFDFF97A17EFDB347615289F9E4" box="[517,648,1624,1648]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="389">B. salicifolia</emphasis>
; the galls are glabrous and globose, 
<quantity id="F2439B0AFF97A17EFE6047445230F907" box="[470,561,1660,1684]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="389" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1-2 mm</quantity>
in diameter, yellowish, hollow (
<figureCitation id="AD802A6AFF97A17EFEEA47A651A1F923" box="[348,416,1694,1719]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="5.[311,323,1805,1824]" captionTargetBox="[228,1362,420,1770]" captionTargetId="figure-15@5.[228,1362,1012,1770]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3: Baccharis salicifolia: top, leaf galls, bottom, twig galls elicited by Aceria cortiiAmrine &amp; Stasny." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5402583" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5402583/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="389">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="350436EFFF97A17AFF7347ED51DFFE01" blockId="3.[159,762,1749,1949]" lastBlockId="7.[159,762,311,405]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="393" pageId="3" pageNumber="389">
<bibRefCitation id="512A4B1EFF97A17EFF7347ED520DF979" author="Kieffer J. J. &amp; Jorgensen P." box="[197,524,1749,1774]" pageId="3" pageNumber="389" pagination="362 - 445" refId="ref4655" refString="Kieffer J. J., Jorgensen P. 1910 - Gallen und Gallentiere aus Argentinien - Centralblatt fuer Bakteriologie, Parasitenkunde und Infektionskrankheiten, 27: 362 - 445." type="journal article" year="1910">Kieffer &amp; Jorgensen (1910</bibRefCitation>
, p. 374) referred to &quot;Eriophyidengallen&quot; on 
<emphasis id="07CFEAFDFF97A17EFE5747C052B6F884" box="[481,695,1784,1808]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="389">Baccharis salicifolia</emphasis>
from 
<collectingRegion id="F77FF80DFF97A17EFF2946235111F8A7" box="[159,272,1819,1843]" country="Argentina" name="Mendoza" pageId="3" pageNumber="389">Mendoza</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="4DAC767FFF97A17EFE944623519DF8A7" box="[290,412,1819,1843]" name="Argentina" pageId="3" pageNumber="389">Argentina</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="512A4B1EFF97A17EFE0E462352D0F8A7" author="Kieffer J. J. &amp; Herbst P." box="[440,721,1819,1843]" pageId="3" pageNumber="389" pagination="696 - 704" refId="ref4686" refString="Kieffer J. J., Herbst P. 1911 - Ueber Gallen und Gallentiere aus Chile - Centralblatt fuer Bakteriologie, Parasitenkunde und Infektionskrankheiten, 29: 696 - 704." type="journal article" year="1911">Kieffer &amp; Herbst (1911</bibRefCitation>
, p. 703) refer to the galls mentioned in the previous paper, however inform that they were collected from 
<emphasis id="07CFEAFDFF97A17EFF6946BC51ABF808" box="[223,426,1924,1948]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="389">Baccharis subulata</emphasis>
D. Don ex Hook. &amp; Arn. (= 
<emphasis id="07CFEAFDFF97A17EFC8C44C753F1F982" box="[826,1008,1535,1559]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="389">Baccharis juncea</emphasis>
(Cass.) Desf.), and which they attribute to 
<taxonomicName id="F2BB4D6CFF97A17EFC07471A549DF9AE" authority="Flechtmann &amp; Arana &amp; Ciarrocchi &amp; Chetverikov &amp; Amrine Jr., 2015" authorityName="Flechtmann &amp; Arana &amp; Ciarrocchi &amp; Chetverikov &amp; Amrine Jr." authorityYear="2015" box="[945,1180,1570,1594]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Eriophyes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baccharidis" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="07CFEAFDFF97A17EFC07471A549DF9AE" box="[945,1180,1570,1594]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="389">Eriophyes baccharidis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="1CFC5786FF97A17EFB13471A54DFF9AD" box="[1189,1246,1570,1593]" pageId="3" pageNumber="389" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but, they only described the gall. 
<bibRefCitation id="512A4B1EFF97A17EFB9E477D5548F9C9" author="Amrine Jr. J. W. &amp; Stasny T. A." box="[1064,1353,1605,1629]" pageId="3" pageNumber="389" refId="ref4118" refString="Amrine Jr. J. W., Stasny T. A. 1994 - Catalog of the Eriophyoidea (Acarina: Prostigmata) of the world - West Bloomfield, Michigan: Indira. 798 pp." type="book" year="1994">Amrine &amp; Stasny (1994)</bibRefCitation>
made a new combination, transferring the mite species to 
<taxonomicName id="F2BB4D6CFF97A17EFC8C47B35401F937" authorityName="Flechtmann" authorityYear="1983" baseAuthorityName="Kieffer &amp; Herbst" baseAuthorityYear="1911" box="[826,1024,1675,1699]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aceria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baccharidis">
<emphasis id="07CFEAFDFF97A17EFC8C47B35401F937" box="[826,1024,1675,1699]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="389">Aceria baccharidis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and updated the host plant name to 
<emphasis id="07CFEAFDFF97A17EFCEA47965412F952" box="[860,1043,1710,1734]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="389">Baccharis juncea</emphasis>
. At this point we do not have sufficient information to further comment on 
<taxonomicName id="F2BB4D6CFF97A17EFAF947E953B3F898" authorityName="Flechtmann" authorityYear="1983" baseAuthorityName="Kieffer &amp; Herbst" baseAuthorityYear="1911" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aceria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baccharidis">
<emphasis id="07CFEAFDFF97A17EFAF947E953B3F898" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="389">Aceria baccharidis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: there is no description nor figure of the mite, no material (gall or mite) from 
<emphasis id="07CFEAFDFF97A17EFB5F4620554DF8BB" box="[1257,1356,1816,1839]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="389">B. juncea</emphasis>
exists and 
<bibRefCitation id="512A4B1EFF97A17EFCDA46025481F8C6" author="Amrine Jr. J. W. &amp; Stasny T. A." box="[876,1152,1850,1874]" pageId="3" pageNumber="389" refId="ref4118" refString="Amrine Jr. J. W., Stasny T. A. 1994 - Catalog of the Eriophyoidea (Acarina: Prostigmata) of the world - West Bloomfield, Michigan: Indira. 798 pp." type="book" year="1994">Amrine &amp; Stasny (1994)</bibRefCitation>
maintained this species distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="F2BB4D6CFF97A17EFC5446665440F8E1" box="[994,1089,1886,1909]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aceria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cortii">
<emphasis id="07CFEAFDFF97A17EFC5446665440F8E1" box="[994,1089,1886,1909]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="389">A. cortii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Specimens from 
<emphasis id="07CFEAFDFF97A17EFA9846655381F80C" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="389">Baccharis juncea</emphasis>
in 
<collectingRegion id="F77FF80DFF97A17EFC1546B85415F80C" box="[931,1044,1920,1944]" country="Argentina" name="Mendoza" pageId="3" pageNumber="389">Mendoza</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="4DAC767FFF97A17EFBA946B85497F80C" box="[1055,1174,1920,1944]" name="Argentina" pageId="3" pageNumber="389">Argentina</collectingCountry>
need to be found and carefully described. If conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="F2BB4D6CFF93A17AFDDB400F52F2FEDA" box="[621,755,311,334]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aceria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="393" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cortii">
<emphasis id="07CFEAFDFF93A17AFDDB400F52F2FEDA" box="[621,755,311,334]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="393">Aceria cortii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, then 
<taxonomicName id="F2BB4D6CFF93A17AFF6A406252CDFEE6" authority="(Kieffer &amp; Herbst, 1911)" authorityName="Flechtmann" authorityYear="1983" baseAuthorityName="Kieffer &amp; Herbst" baseAuthorityYear="1911" box="[220,716,346,370]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aceria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="393" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baccharidis">
<emphasis id="07CFEAFDFF93A17AFF6A406251A5FEE6" box="[220,420,346,370]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="393">Aceria baccharidis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="512A4B1EFF93A17AFE02406252C5FEE6" author="Kieffer J. J. &amp; Herbst P." box="[436,708,346,370]" pageId="7" pageNumber="393" pagination="696 - 704" refId="ref4686" refString="Kieffer J. J., Herbst P. 1911 - Ueber Gallen und Gallentiere aus Chile - Centralblatt fuer Bakteriologie, Parasitenkunde und Infektionskrankheiten, 29: 696 - 704." type="journal article" year="1911">Kieffer &amp; Herbst, 1911</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
becomes the senior synonym.
</paragraph>
